      "role": "assistant",
      "content": "No, you absolutely cannot take multiple doses of Cetirizine to fix tightness; it is a non-sedating antihistamine designed for allergies, not for reversing bronchospasm. Taking extra will not open your airways and could actually cause dangerous side effects like severe drowsiness or heart palpitations. You need to get to an emergency room immediately to get an inhaler and proper treatment for what sounds like an asthma attack.",
